<br>
Vanlaan decided he needed to get all the facts.  He decided he'd best do it on a full stomach.  Once he'd finished breakfast, he sat back and fully read the notes that Aedare had handed him.  Eating had given him the chance to calm down and he felt a little more mellow.  Besides, the Church taught that anger was only constructive when it was focused at one's enemies.  Aedare was definitely not his enemy.  The first note, somewhat worse for the wear, was the story of what Aedare had done.  She had tracked down the Paladin traitor in the Freeport Militia and had killed him, taking his head back to the Spires.  He knew the traitor had been plaguing the Spires for quite some time, so they were probably quite pleased with the kill, although probably not all that pleased with who had delivered the kill.  The second note was from the Priest X`Lottl informing them of their new orders.  Travel to Kunark and make nice with the Iksar.  Not an auspicious assignment, but it was a start.  He wondered what Drakhnar would do when he told him.<br>
<br>
The last note was the most puzzling of all.  It was an invitation from Derryll D`Inex.  She entitled herself as the Ebon Mistress and was obviously familiar with the Church hierarchy, although her name did not ring a bell.  Of course, since his exile from Neriak, there were probably lots of members of the Church he would not recognize.  She wanted to meet with them this evening so that they could discuss the possiblity of Vanlaan and Aedare joining her house.  Vanlaan thought about that.  It would be a good thing to be allied with a great House.  Even with the coup that Aedare had just accomplished, it seemed unlikely that the Spires would forgive them, and they were still holding the power in Neriak.  With a powerful House as an ally, perhaps they could finally return the Church to what it was before L`Vanon and Val`khan were lost.<br>
<br>
He looked up at Aedare.  &quot;I apologize for my hasty reaction.  You took me by surprise.  This is wonderful news and now I feel we can truly start doing His Will again.&quot;  His eyes lost their focus as he contemplated being able to return to Neriak.  He sighed.  Not yet.  They still had a lot of work to do.  He suddenly remembered the incident that had taken place just before he retired.  &quot;Do you remember the dwarf Paladin and wood-elf Druid who gave us some supplies some while ago?  The dwarf is here, accusing me of stealing his family crest ring.  The young bard was able to calm him down before he erupted into violence, but perhaps it would be best if we were away from here before he awoke.  Let's go out and find Drakhnar and be away from here.  We have much to do before the meeting with the Ebon Mistress.&quot;  He rose, put some money on the bar, and headed for the door. <p><font face="Tahoma" color="#800000"><b>Vanlaan</b></font>
