ws themselves began to gather at the feet of the hapless human.  Up they climbed and the militaman finaly found his quarry.  Before he could take one step, Drakhnar chanted another quick spell, this time the very ground opened up before the militaman...who's face was beginning to fill with horror as he looked down and saw death itself claw its way free with boney fingers.  His terror was furthered when he tried to back away, only to find his legs were being consumed by the very shadows.  They spread upwards, consuming his torso, he franticly tried to brush them off, only to have them consume his hands and spread up his arms.  Desprately he tried to swing at the skeleton that was now standing in front of him...only to find his very face being covered in darkness.   Drakhnar chanted another spell.  The militiaman crumpled to his knees and began to claw at his chest, his very heart felt as if it was going to explode.  He tried to crawl away.  Drakhnar pointed at the militiaman, this was all that was needed for the skeleton that was standing by, watching, to spring to life.  Mercelessly it began to claw at the militiaman's armor, pummeling him without end, cackleing gleefully.  Drakhnar chanted another spell, and the militiaman doubled over in pain as scalding blood poured forth from his nostrils and ears.   Drakhnar watched as his pet tore through the armor of the militaman and began to rend his very flesh from his bones.  Drakhnar quietly chanted one final spell and the militiaman was engulfed in the familiar green haze.  Once again time seemed to slow to a crawl.  The shadows that had consumed the man begin to fade....just in time for Drakhnar to see the life fading from his eye's.  This victims life was MUCH stonger than that little birds and Drakhnar felt it pulse through his body in a manner that was almost orgasmic.  Drakhnar sighed as he let a smile appear on his face.   Quickly he regained his composure and began to inspect his victim.  The man, or more appropriately, his corpse, did not yeild very much information, though it did yeild a few peices of platinum and a nice sword that Drakhnar would be more than happy to sell.  &quot;Fool&quot; Drakhnar said as we waved his hand in a dismissing manner....sending his pet back from where it came.   &quot;Oh well&quot; he hissed, &quot;Guesssss that is enough ressst for one morning.&quot;  And with that, Drakhnar chanted another spell, quickly concealing himself in the shadows as he walked towards the inn. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucasidy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Casidy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/23/01 11:01:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=63>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yet another beginning...</span><hr size=1> A messenger had arrived before the sun rose, and had carried a message on the notes of morning to Casidy.<br>
<br>
It has woken her from her slumber.<br>
<br>
She had risen quickly, and had traveled in the dark to the mentioned spot in the tunnel to meet the member of the guild.<br>
<br>
She had understood the message, and had returned to the inn to gather her things.<br>
<br>
She walked back into the inn and noticed the lady at the table from the evening before.<br>
<br>
Perhaps she could be persuaded to accompany me on this quest. Pondering these thoughts Casidy smiled and asked the strange lady if she might share her table.<br>
<br>
Indicating to the barmaid to bring around some hot tea and some fresh muffins with the wave of her hand, and not waiting for the reply, Casidy sat down across from the lady.<br>
<br>
"G'morning, my name is Casidy might I ask what brings you to these parts of the commonlands traveler?"<br>
<br>
